Patch Set 3: Code-Review-2

(2 comments)

The Glance PTL has asked us to -2 trivial changes to reduce pressure on the gates until the stable branch for newton is cut.

In the meantime, there are a few things you could do with this patch.

(1) The problem you've identified could be handled as a bugfix to the doc tools (see my comment on PS2--there's already a bug filed for this, maybe you could tackle fixing it?).

(2) I tried a workaround, but I think the workaround shows that the api-ref tool probably has a bug handling unicode in headings.  You might want to test that out and file a bug (and fix it if you're motivated!).

(3) "List all images" isn't quite accurate as a title for this call.  But if neither of the bugs above are fixed soon, I'd prefer that your patch change the v2 api-ref to have "List images" for this call, and change the v1 api-ref (which will be deprecated in Newton) to have either "Show images" or "List all images".  That way the "compromise" language will be on the api-ref least likely to be used, instead of on the api-ref for the current version.

So I will do as 2 directions:
- Change v1/ to "list all images" as your suggest
- OR Change config.py to each v1/ and v2/ and config tox.ini
Can you suggest me which path I can follow?
